I respect that.

652
00:48:53,635 --> 00:48:55,235
哦,什么?我们现在是朋友吗?
Oh, what? We're buddies now?

653
00:48:55,269 --> 00:48:58,506
让我猜猜，你有恋父情结吗?
Let me guess, you got some kind of a daddy issue?

654
00:49:01,208 --> 00:49:05,112
我和我父亲的关系…复杂。
My relationship with my father is... complicated.

655
00:49:05,145 --> 00:49:09,684
当他不忙着喝酒和揍我的时候，我们在成长过程中确实有点园艺天赋。
When he wasn't busy drinking and kicking my ass, we did have a bit of a green thumb growing up.

656
00:49:09,717 --> 00:49:14,221
你看，种植土壤，是个藏炸弹的好地方。
You see, planter soil, it's a great place to hide a bomb.

657
00:49:15,790 --> 00:49:19,861
24小时不间断的新闻最棒的地方在于，坏人还是可以看的。
And the best part about 24/7 news is that the bad guys get to watch it all the same.

658
00:49:19,894 --> 00:49:27,902
所以他们在这种情况下做的第一件事就是扫视这片区域，但是肥料炸弹，埋在几英尺深的土壤下是不会被发现的。
So the first thing they do in our situation is sweep the area, but a fertilizer bomb, that doesn't show up when it's under a few feet of soil.

659
00:49:27,936 --> 00:49:33,842
你现在就把供词读出来，不然我就按下红色小按钮把你的家人变成汤。
So you read that confession now, or I press my little red button and turn your family into soup.

660
00:49:33,875 --> 00:49:36,076
好了，够了，够了。
All right, enough, enough.

661
00:49:40,247 --> 00:49:42,115
你想让我读这个吗?
You want me to read this?

662
00:49:42,951 --> 00:49:45,920
是的，那太好了。
Yes, that would be great.

663
00:49:45,954 --> 00:49:50,090
奥兰多，我们来点轻松的即兴表演吧。
Oh, and Orlando, let's take it light on the improv.

664
00:49:50,123 --> 00:49:54,963
我是一个非常严格遵守诺言的人。
I'm a real stickler for my words.

665
00:49:54,995 --> 00:49:58,766
有人告诉我，我们接到了来自哈德逊大厦的电话。
I'm being told that we're getting a call from within Hudson Tower.

666
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:02,236
有可能有人被困在大楼里。
It could possibly be that there is someone trapped inside the building.

667
00:50:02,269 --> 00:50:04,037
打电话的人，你叫什么名字?
Caller, what is your name?

668
00:50:05,239 --> 00:50:07,274
这是住十楼的那个人。
This is the man on the tenth floor.

669
00:50:07,307 --> 00:50:11,011
我要你把我马上发给你的这段视频直播下去。
I want you to go live with this feed I'm about to send you.

670
00:50:19,486 --> 00:50:21,121
嘿,佐伊。
Hey, Zoey.

671
00:50:21,154 --> 00:50:25,301
我的搭档，杰克逊警官，他想问你几个问题。这里有点闷。
My partner, Officer Jackson here, he wants to ask you a few questions. It's kind of stuffy in here.

672
00:50:25,325 --> 00:50:27,662
你为什么不出去呼吸点新鲜空气，吃点零食?
Why don't you go out and get some fresh air, maybe a snack?

673
00:50:27,695 --> 00:50:29,129
你觉得呢?
What do you think?

674
00:50:29,162 --> 00:50:31,533
-你感觉怎么样?——没关系。你可以走了。
- What do you feel like? - It's okay. You can go.

675
00:50:31,566 --> 00:50:32,634
是吗?
Yeah?

676
00:50:38,673 --> 00:50:42,342
-没有不重要的工作，英雄。-连当保姆都不行。
- No job too small, hero. - Not even babysitting.

677
00:50:45,112 --> 00:50:48,550
夫人……警长想和你谈谈。
Ma'am... Chief wants to talk to you.

678
00:50:48,583 --> 00:50:55,222
弗莱尔女士，我需要知道你丈夫的一切，如果他能做出这种事。
Ms. Friar, I need to know everything about your husband, and if he's capable of doing something like this.

679
00:50:55,255 --> 00:50:57,525
不，这里不是奥兰多。
No, this isn't Orlando.

680
00:50:57,559 --> 00:50:59,126
他有案底。
Well, he has record.

681
00:50:59,159 --> 00:51:01,161
我知道他的记录，好吗?
Yeah, I'm aware of his record, okay?

682
00:51:01,194 --> 00:51:09,871
是的，他有一些问题，但他试图改变，他非常努力地扭转局面。
And yes, he has some red marks, but he's tried to change, and he's worked really hard to turn things around.

683
00:51:09,904 --> 00:51:11,438
他的尝试。
He's trying.

684
00:51:11,471 --> 00:51:15,175
所以他在成为证人之前就会被起诉吗?
So he was going to be prosecuted before he turned witness?

685
00:51:16,945 --> 00:51:18,546
嗯,是的。
Um, yeah.

686
00:51:19,714 --> 00:51:30,058
这是,嗯……我在计划…给他一个…但这里不是奥兰多。
It was, um... I was planning, um... on giving him a... But this isn't Orlando.

687
00:51:30,123 --> 00:51:32,594
——我知道。-你怎么知道?
- I know. - How do you know?

688
00:51:32,627 --> 00:51:40,802
因为奥兰多犯了一些非常愚蠢的错误，但他不会冒险失去佐伊。
Because Orlando has made some really stupid mistakes, but the one thing he wouldn't risk losing is Zoey.

689
00:51:40,835 --> 00:51:42,135
看，这对我很有效。
See, that works for me.

690
00:51:42,169 --> 00:51:44,171
不符合这种工作的特征。
Doesn't fit the profile of a gig like this.

691
00:51:44,204 --> 00:51:46,074
我们根据现有的情报。
We're going off present intel.

692
00:51:46,106 --> 00:51:47,976
我给他打电话，他也想给我打电话。
I called and he tried to call me.

693
00:51:48,009 --> 00:51:49,877
我错过了。
Um, I missed it.

694
00:51:51,980 --> 00:51:53,881
队长，你得看看这个。
Chief, you gotta look at this here.

695
00:51:53,915 --> 00:51:55,282
头了。
Heads up.

696
00:51:56,050 --> 00:51:58,886
我叫奥兰多·弗莱尔。
My name is Orlando Friar.

697
00:51:58,920 --> 00:52:04,692
我是对公园和哈德逊大厦爆炸案负责的人。
I am the person responsible for the bombing in the park and Hudson Towers.

698
00:52:04,726 --> 00:52:09,396
大楼里还有更多的炸弹，藏在全城各处。
There are more bombs in the building and hidden throughout the city.

699
00:52:09,429 --> 00:52:15,637
任何不速之客的闯入都会导致数百人死亡。
Any more intrusions from unwanted guests will result in hundreds of deaths.

700
00:52:15,670 --> 00:52:17,705
我希望我讲清楚了。
I hope I am clear.

701
00:52:19,139 --> 00:52:24,679
我骗了你们所有人，骗了我妻子金，骗了我女儿佐伊。
I have lied to all of you, to my wife, Kim, to my daughter, Zoey.

702
00:52:25,880 --> 00:52:30,885
我协助策划了我们历史上最严重的一次金融诈骗。
I helped orchestrate one of the worst financial deceptions in public trust in our history.

703
00:52:31,819 --> 00:52:34,354
首先，我想定下一些基本规则。
First, I want to set some ground rules.

704
00:52:36,189 --> 00:52:37,859
我已准备好赴死。
I am prepared to die.

705
00:52:39,292 --> 00:52:41,461
我被一个死人的开关钩住了。
I am hooked to a dead man's switch.

706
00:52:42,730 --> 00:52:49,169
如果你杀了我，就会引爆所有炸弹…这将是一个血腥的圣诞节
If you kill me, it will trigger all bombs... and it will be a bloody Christmas.

707
00:52:50,538 --> 00:52:54,042
金,佐伊……我爱你!
Kim, Zoey... I love you!

708
00:52:54,075 --> 00:52:55,710
我很抱歉……
I'm sorry...

709
00:52:58,278 --> 00:53:01,649
这里不是奥兰多。他是吓坏了。
This is not Orlando. He is terrified.

710
00:53:01,683 --> 00:53:04,184
-让所有炸弹技术人员准备突破。- - - - - -。
- Get every single bomb tech ready to breach. - On it.

711
00:53:04,217 --> 00:53:06,253
好了，特警，准备袭击。
All right, SWAT, prep for assault.

712
00:53:07,387 --> 00:53:08,790
-等待…——走吧。
- Wait... - Let's go.

713
00:53:08,823 --> 00:53:10,625
拜托，听我说。
Please, just listen to me.

714
00:53:10,658 --> 00:53:13,293
你到底在想什么?
What the hell were you thinking?

715
00:53:13,326 --> 00:53:15,328
你想让你的家人死吗?
Do you want your family to die?

716
00:53:15,362 --> 00:53:17,532
我告诉过你要仔细阅读那一页的内容!
I told you to read exactly what was on that page!

717
00:53:17,565 --> 00:53:20,233
一个准备引爆自己的人是不会动摇的。
A man ready to blow himself up doesn't waver.

718
00:53:20,267 --> 00:53:22,469
那你打算怎么做?
And what are you gonna do about it?

719
00:53:22,502 --> 00:53:25,673
你觉得有办法逃出去吗，混蛋!
Oh, you think there's a way out of this, motherfucker?!

720
00:53:25,707 --> 00:53:29,777
你以为我不会再追杀你和你的小家庭了吗?
You think I won't hunt you and your shitty little family down again?

721
00:53:36,117 --> 00:53:37,685
时钟的滴答声。
Clock's ticking.

722
00:53:44,092 --> 00:53:46,326
你们在说什么?
What were you talking about?

723
00:53:54,401 --> 00:54:00,942
两年前，奥兰多，他和一个…在纽约开了一家大公司
Two years ago, uh, Orlando, he signed on with a... with a big bucks New York startup.

724
00:54:00,975 --> 00:54:07,481
好吧?他们支付了我们所有的账单，这比奥兰多以前的黑客生活好多了。
Okay? And they paid all of our bills, and it was better than Orlando's former life in hacking.

725
00:54:08,616 --> 00:54:11,351
投资银行家，退休老人。
Investment bankers, old retirees.

726
00:54:11,384 --> 00:54:14,055
任何有投资组合的人都受到欢迎。
Anyone with portfolios was welcome.

727
00:54:14,088 --> 00:54:17,491
旧的钱，纽约的钱。
Old money, New York money.

728
00:54:17,525 --> 00:54:20,260
这一切都应该受到法律的规范。
It was all supposed to be regulated, by the books.

729
00:54:20,293 --> 00:54:24,999
但我们很快就意识到为什么他们如此渴望奥兰多。
But we soon realized why they wanted Orlando so badly.

730
00:54:25,032 --> 00:54:30,872
他们利用我黑进手机，黑进服务器。
They used me to crack into phones, to break into servers.

731
00:54:30,905 --> 00:54:32,740
任何事情都可以获得优势。
Anything to gain an edge.

732
00:54:34,274 --> 00:54:36,043
我以为对他们来说只是数据挖掘。
I thought it was just data mining for them.

733
00:54:37,211 --> 00:54:43,316
但事实证明，他们侵入了人们的储蓄……401 ks。
But it turns out they were hacking into people's savings... their 401ks.

734
00:54:44,085 --> 00:54:45,686
你不知道吗?
And you didn't know?

735
00:54:47,555 --> 00:54:48,723
我,嗯…
I, uh...

736
00:54:51,458 --> 00:54:54,427
我任性地天真。
I was willfully naive.

737
00:54:55,196 --> 00:54:57,265
我是说，他们都是有权势的人。
I mean, these were powerful people.

738
00:54:57,297 --> 00:55:00,868
你知道，华尔街的政客们。
You know, Wall Street, politicians.

739
00:55:03,037 --> 00:55:07,141
一旦联邦调查局介入，我就不能再让他们抢劫了。
Once the Feds got involved, I couldn't outright let them rob anyone anymore.

740
00:55:07,175 --> 00:55:10,477
那……买股票的人呢?
And what about... The people who bought in?

741
00:55:10,511 --> 00:55:14,381
破产了，被他们信任的体制吞噬了。
Broke, and eaten by the system they trusted.

742
00:55:14,414 --> 00:55:19,554
不仅仅是有钱的投资者，还有普通人。
And it wasn't just rich investors, it was regular people.

743
00:55:19,587 --> 00:55:22,990
他们的未来，他们的养老金，都没了。
Their futures, their pensions, just gone.

744
00:55:23,024 --> 00:55:28,196
我为那些偷钱和花钱一样快的骗子工作。
I worked for crooks who spent it as fast as they stole it.

745
00:55:28,229 --> 00:55:30,463
没有什么可以回馈的。
There was nothing to give back.

746
00:55:30,497 --> 00:55:33,868
没办法让这些人重获新生。
No way to give these people their lives back.

747
00:55:35,136 --> 00:55:37,370
我们把老板抓起来了。
We put the bosses away.

748
00:55:39,140 --> 00:55:41,542
我和我的搭档达成了协议。
And me and my partner took a deal.

749
00:55:46,379 --> 00:55:47,815
我接受了一个协议。
I took a deal.

750
00:55:47,849 --> 00:55:51,384
你这么做是为了你的家人。
You did what you had to for your family.

751
00:55:55,289 --> 00:55:58,192
当他发现他们在做什么的时候，他就把他们告发了。
When he found out what they were doing, he turned them in.

752
00:55:58,226 --> 00:56:02,330
他没有想到他自己，也没有想到他即将失去的家人。
He didn't think about himself or the family he was about to lose.

753
00:56:02,362 --> 00:56:05,498
我们离开了城市，搬到了这里。
And we left the city and we moved here.

754
00:56:06,433 --> 00:56:10,738
他骗了我，但他最后做了正确的事。
He lied to me, but, um, he did the right thing in the end.

755
00:56:10,771 --> 00:56:13,040
他是个好人。
He's a good man.

756
00:56:13,074 --> 00:56:14,709
他是。
He is.

757
00:56:14,742 --> 00:56:16,409
上膛，上膛。
Locked and loaded, Chief.

758
00:56:16,443 --> 00:56:17,678
绿色的光。
Green light.

759
00:56:17,712 --> 00:56:19,280
绿灯吗?发生了什么?
Green light? What is happening?

760
00:56:19,313 --> 00:56:20,891
好了，你得出去，拜托了。
All right, you need to go outside, please.

761
00:56:20,915 --> 00:56:23,483
-请不要伤害我丈夫。-听着，这不是我们能决定的
- Please don't hurt my husband. - Listen, it's not up to us.

762
00:56:23,517 --> 00:56:26,854
这取决于他。他要么现在结束这一切，要么我们替他结束。
It's up to him. He can either end this now or we'll end it for him.

763
00:56:30,191 --> 00:56:32,126
谁能把她弄出去?
Can somebody get her outside?

764
00:56:33,460 --> 00:56:34,862
——妈妈。——佐伊。
- Mom. - Zoey.

765
00:56:34,896 --> 00:56:37,665
你告诉他们爸爸给我们的留言了吗?
Did you tell them about the message that Dad left us?

766
00:56:37,698 --> 00:56:43,371
是的…是的，他打了电话，还留了言，听起来好像有人在后台。
Yeah... yes, he-he-he called and he left a message, and, um, it sounds like there's someone in the background.

767
00:56:43,403 --> 00:56:44,572
只是听。
Just listen.

768
00:56:44,605 --> 00:56:46,406
嘿，嘿，大家小声点，好吗?
Hey, hey, everyone, keep it down, will you?

769
00:56:46,439 --> 00:56:49,409
嘿，奥兰多，你很有名。
Hey, Orlando, you're famous.

770
00:56:49,442 --> 00:56:50,945
-我的天啊-我听到了。
- Oh, my God. - I hear him.

771
00:56:50,978 --> 00:56:53,581
我听说有人在那里跟他说话。
I hear there's somebody there talking to him.

772
00:56:53,614 --> 00:56:55,750
好吧，我们会考虑的。
All right, we'll take it into consideration.

773
00:56:55,783 --> 00:56:58,819
-你会帮我爸爸吗?-是的，我们会尽力的。在这里。
- Will you help my dad? - Yeah, we'll do our best. Here.

774
00:57:00,221 --> 00:57:02,757
我试着联系大楼经理，埃德蒙·哈里斯。
I tried to reach the building manager, Edmond Harris.

775
00:57:02,790 --> 00:57:05,458
没有人知道他在哪里。甚至他的家人。
No one knows where he is. Even his family.

776
00:57:05,492 --> 00:57:06,794
可能是炸弹客。
Could be the bomber.

777
00:57:08,162 --> 00:57:11,132
局长，我们得在今天有人死之前干掉这混蛋。
Chief, we gotta take this fucker before anybody else dies today.

778
00:57:11,165 --> 00:57:13,500
他说他有个死人的开关随时会爆炸。
He says he's got a dead man's switch ready to blow.

779
00:57:13,534 --> 00:57:16,270
如果我们杀了他，谁知道还会死多少人?
If we kill him, who knows how many more could die?

780
00:57:16,304 --> 00:57:19,140
我们刚才在电话里听到的那个声音，可能是他在发号施令。
That voice we just heard on the phone, he could be calling the shots.

781
00:57:19,173 --> 00:57:21,042
你想试试吗?
You want to take that chance?

782
00:57:21,075 --> 00:57:24,779
你觉得奥兰多是替罪羊吗?
Now do you think maybe Orlando's the patsy?

783
00:57:24,812 --> 00:57:27,480
队长，你看了情况报告。这他妈是虚张声势!
Chief, you read the sitrep. It's a fucking bluff!

784
00:57:27,515 --> 00:57:33,688
我们不会坐在这里听这些年迈的，过气的拆弹小组的人说他们还没有从他们该死的过去中恢复过来。
We're not gonna sit here and listen to these old, washed up bomb squad guys that haven't recovered from their fucked up past.

785
00:57:33,721 --> 00:57:36,524
嘿，这不公平。杰克逊还没老，也没完蛋。
Hey, that's not fair. Jackson's not old and washed up.

786
00:57:36,557 --> 00:57:38,159
好了，给我闭嘴。
Okay, shut the fuck up.

787
00:57:39,459 --> 00:57:44,632
96年圣诞节，第一个电话，家庭纠纷。
Christmas '96, first call, domestic disturbance.

788
00:57:44,665 --> 00:57:48,468
那家伙说如果我们采取行动，他会把房子和孩子都炸了。
Guy said that if we made a move, he'd blow the house, kids at all.

789
00:57:48,501 --> 00:57:52,273
